<item>
            <title>[SPARK-10865] [Spark SQL] [UDF] the ceil/ceiling function got wrong return value type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10865</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per ceil/ceiling definition,it should get BIGINT return value&lt;br/&gt;
-ceil(DOUBLE a), ceiling(DOUBLE a)&lt;br/&gt;
-Returns the minimum BIGINT value that is equal to or greater than a.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in current Spark implementation, it got wrong value type.&lt;br/&gt;
e.g., &lt;br/&gt;
select ceil(2642.12) from udf_test_web_sales limit 1;&lt;br/&gt;
2643.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In hive implementation, it got return value type like below:&lt;br/&gt;
hive&amp;gt; select ceil(2642.12) from udf_test_web_sales limit 1;&lt;br/&gt;
OK&lt;br/&gt;
2643&lt;/p&gt;</description>
