                            <comment id="14934552" author="apachespark" created="Tue, 29 Sep 2015 03:19:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;chenghao-intel&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8933&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8933&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14934584" author="srowen" created="Tue, 29 Sep 2015 03:47:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this really different from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10866&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10866&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14936799" author="0x0fff" created="Wed, 30 Sep 2015 12:48:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t really think that &lt;em&gt;floor()&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;ceiling()&lt;/em&gt; should return integer data type. For instance, in &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.oracle.com/cd/E11882_01/server.112/e10592/functions067.htm#SQLRF00643&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Oracle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.5/static/functions-math.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Postgres&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms178531.aspx&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;MS SQL&lt;/a&gt; these functions return the same data type provided as input&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14940218" author="davies" created="Thu, 1 Oct 2015 18:48:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved by pull request 8933&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8933&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/8933&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15000404" author="dricard" created="Wed, 11 Nov 2015 14:07:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it possible for this fix to be included in the 1.5.2 release? This is causing major issues with some BI Tool that apply transformation and expect an INT from Ceil.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15001422" author="chenghao" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2015 00:43:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We actually follow the criteria of Hive, and actually I tested it in MySQL, it works in the same way. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15001423" author="chenghao" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2015 00:44:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1.5.2 is released, I am not sure whether part of it now or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
